The input integers `m` and `n` must be greater than or equal to 1.
The length of the `guards` array must be greater than or equal to 1.
The length of the `walls` array must be greater than or equal to 1.
The sum of the lengths of the `guards` and `walls` arrays must be less than or equal to `m * n`.
The positions in the `guards` and `walls` arrays must be within the bounds of the grid, i.e., `0 <= row_i < m` and `0 <= col_i < n`.
All positions in the `guards` and `walls` arrays must be unique.
